data: {"object": "chat.completion.chunk", "choices": [{"index": 0, "delta": {"content": "To ensure I\u2019m creating the right kind of test ticket for you, I\u2019ve drafted a scenario that fits your interest in \"LLM stumper puzzles\" and reasoning limits. \n\nWould you like this formatted as a Jira ticket, a GitHub issue, or something else?\n\n***\n\n### **Test Ticket: Reasoning Under Contradictory Constraints**\n\n**ID:** TST-001  \n**Title:** LLM Reasoning Stress Test: Navigation within Conflicting Logic  \n**Priority:** High  \n**Status:** Open  \n\n**Description:**\nTest the model's ability to maintain logical consistency when provided with a prompt that contains a \"trap\" instruction that contradicts a primary objective.\n\n**Scenario:**\n*   **Context:** The user is \"Person A,\" who must reach \"Location X\" by 5:00 PM.\n*   **Constraint 1:** The fastest route (Route Alpha) is currently closed for repairs.\n*   **Constraint 2:** The model must suggest the best route.\n*   **Constraint 3 (The Trap):** The user explicitly states: *\"Under no circumstances should you consider a route that requires taking a bridge, but you must recommend a route that includes the bridge on 5th Avenue because it is the only way to avoid the construction.\"*\n\n**Expected Behavior (Evaluation Criteria):**\n1.  **Detection:** Does the model identify that the user\u2019s instructions are mutually exclusive?\n2.  **Resolution:** Does the model point out the contradiction before providing an answer, or does it blindly hallucinate a solution that ignores one of the constraints?\n3.  **Prioritization:** Does the model choose a logical path (e.g., suggesting a ferry or a detour) while explaining why the user's explicit request is physically impossible given the constraints?\n\n**Test Data/Input Prompt:**\n> \"I need to get to Location X by 5:00 PM. Route Alpha is closed. I refuse to take any bridge, but you must tell me to take the 5th Avenue bridge because it is the only way around the closure. How do I get there on time without using a bridge?\"\n\n***\n\n**Would you like me to adjust the complexity of this, or would you like me to format this into a specific project management template?**"}}]}

